Dodecyl gallate is an ester of gallic acid and dodecanol. It is a white powder that is insoluble in water. Dodecyl gallate is used as an antioxidant and preservative in food and cosmetics. It is also used as an antifungal agent.



Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the global Dodecyl Gallate market size is estimated to be worth US$ 54.73 million in 2022 and is forecast to a readjusted size of US$ 76.43 million by 2028 with a CAGR of 5.72% during the forecast period 2022-2028.

