Fully considering the economic change by this health crisis, Purity above 98% accounting for 87.59% of the Dodecyl Gallate global market in 2021, is projected to value US$ 67.10 million by 2028, growing at a revised 5.77% CAGR from 2022 to 2028. While Food segment is altered to an 6.44% CAGR throughout this forecast period.



The major drivers for the growth of the DG market are the growing demand for processed food and the increasing use of DG in cosmetics. The processed food industry is growing due to the changing lifestyle of consumers, who are now opting for ready-to-eat and convenience foods. The cosmetics industry is also growing due to the increasing awareness of personal grooming among consumers.



The main advantage of dodecyl gallate is that it is an effective preservative. It helps to extend the shelf life of food products by preventing the growth of bacteria and other microorganisms. Additionally, dodecyl gallate can help to prevent the oxidation of fats and oils. This can improve the taste and quality of food products.



However, there are some disadvantages to using dodecyl gallate as well. Some research has shown that it may be toxic to human cells in vitro. Additionally, it can migrate from food packaging into the food itself. This can result in increased levels of dodecyl gallate in the diet.

